  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UN Joint-Project to Address Cooking Fuel Needs, Environmental Degradation and Food Security for Populations Affected by the Refugee Crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to address the urgent cooking fuel needs of Rohingya refugees in Cox&apos;s Bazar (Bangladesh), by introducing alternative clean cooking fuel and technology. Through this project, households receive cooking kits, liquid petroleum gas (LPG) refills during the duration of the project and are trained to use their LPG stoves in a safe and efficient manner, whilst receiving nutritional cooking orientation and messaging. Community fire safety teams are established and trained through coordination with the Fire Service and Civil Defense to ensure fire preparedness and response capacity, and to regularly inspect LPG sets in the selected refugee and host community households. Moreover, a comprehensive environmental and social impact study is conducted to mitigate any negative environmental or social impact the project may have.</narrative>
  </description>
